# Domain Spec Sync With Data Model

When changing domain/data model structures, always keep `spec/domain/*.puml` synchronized in the same change set.

## Trigger (must update conceptual specs)

Apply this whenever a change affects conceptual intent in `backend/app/model/**`, including:

- entity added, removed, or renamed
- relationship/cardinality changed
- ownership/context semantics changed
- lifecycle/invariant semantics changed

## Required updates

- Update the relevant focused diagram(s) in `spec/domain/*-domain.puml`.
- Update `spec/domain/conceptual-domain-model.puml` for cross-domain impacts.
- Update `spec/domain/conceptual-paths.puml` when user/business journeys (`P1..P6`) change.
- Keep `spec/domain/README.md` aligned when files or scope change.

## Completion gate

Do not finish model-affecting work unless conceptual specs are updated or you explicitly document why no conceptual change occurred.

